#: 21337012-0-859
msgctxt "21337012-0-859"
msgid ""
"It is very rare for one of our people to be born away from the Hist. We are, "
"in a very real way, part of the Hist. To be born away from it is to be born "
"without something essential. For most of my life and service as a healer, "
"this has remained a theoretical issue. That is, until Ja-Reet.\n"
"\n"
"Though born in slavery, he's done well since the Pact and our emancipation. "
"He even married a Dunmer—the daughter of the Narsis family who owned his "
"parents. While I view such a union with personal distaste, it speaks well of "
"his ability to interact in society despite his obvious disadvantage.\n"
"\n"
"Make no mistake, in Argonian society, he is disadvantaged. He's unable to "
"read social clues, the subtle movements of muscle and tail that most of us "
"take for granted. We occasionally have difficulty reading the emotions of "
"other races. Ja-Reet has that problem even with fellow Argonians. He listens "
"to spoken words, and is insensitive to their tone. Surely being born away "
"from the Hist has deprived him of emotional intuition.\n"
"\n"
"He brought his Elven wife with him to Percolating Mire. She's not welcomed "
"by all, though she draws him out socially, which has been invaluable in "
"trying to learn about how he thinks.\n"
"\n"
"Perhaps proximity to a thriving Hist tree will help Ja-Reet gain the "
"intuition the rest of us take for granted."
msgstr ""
"우리 아르고니안들에게 히스트로부터 떨어진 곳에서 생명이 태어나는 것은 상당히 드물다. 우리들은 아주 현실적인 의미로 히스트의 일부인 "
"것이다. 여기서 떨어져 태어난다는 것은 중요한 무언가가 결여된 채 태어나는 것이다. 인생의 대부분 동안 치료사로서 일을 하는 도중, 이 "
"문제는 이론적인 가능성으로서 항상 있었다. 쟈-리트가 와서 이것이 현실이 되기까지는.\n"
"\n"
"그는 노예로 태어났지만 조약과 노예해방 이후 자주 찾아왔다. 던머와 결혼까지 하였다. 부모를 소유하고 있던 나르시스 가문의 딸하고 말이다."
" 그러한 인연은 개인적으로 불쾌감을 가지고 보았지만, 명확히 불리한 입장에 있으면서도 사회에서 교류해 가는 그의 능력을 높이 사고 있다.\n"
"\n"
"분명히 아르고니안의 사회에서 그는 불리하다. 그는 사회적 단서이며, 우리들의 대부분이 당연한 것으로 여기는 근육이나 꼬리의 미묘한 "
"움직임조차 읽지 못하였다. 다른 종족의 감정을 파악하기 어려운 점은 이따금씩 있지만, 쟈-리트는 아르고니안 동료에게조차 그 문제를 보인다."
" 또한 들리는 이야기에 귀를 기울이지만, 그 목소리에는 무관심하다. 이건 분명 히스트로부터 떨어져 태어났기 때문에, 히스트에게 감정적인 "
"직감을 빼앗겨 버린 것이다.\n"
"\n"
"그는 시간이 지나자 습지에서 엘프 아내를 데리고 돌아갔다. 그녀는 누구에게도 환영받지 못하였지만, 그의 사교성을 끌어낸 것이다. 그녀의 "
"가르침은 그에게 있어 소중한 것 이었다.\n"
"\n"
"활력이 넘치는 히스트 나무에 다가가면, 다른 사람들은 당연하게 가지고 있는 직감을 쟈-리트가 얻기 위해 도움이 될지도 모른다."

#: 51188213-0-859
msgctxt "51188213-0-859"
msgid "The Strange Case of Ja-Reet"
msgstr "쟈-리트의 기묘한 상황"

#: 21337012-0-858
msgctxt "21337012-0-858"
msgid ""
"… with some success. Beem-Tei discovered the hidden entrance to the Dwemer "
"underworks; may her spirit find repose in the waters of Black Marsh. The "
"automatons guard their masters' secrets well.\n"
"\n"
"The spider and sphere guardians swarmed over us, killing Beem-Tei and "
"Reekatul before we fought them off. The outer chamber was ours, for a time. "
"The central heating plant and other machinery were fascinating but Ukka-Malz "
"insisted we press farther in, searching for relics we could remove.\n"
"\n"
"The inner chamber was our undoing. Spheres and spiders were the least of our "
"worries. Our intrusion awakened a Dwemer Centurion. From the inscriptions on "
"the walls, we were able to learn its name just before we were overwhelmed: "
"Thzallek Eft. Ukka-Malz and the others died under its relentless assault. "
"Only I lived to reach the exit. Thzallek Eft. The name will haunt my sleep.\n"
"\n"
"But I cannot get out. The doors are locked by an unseen mechanism. Our food "
"and water are back in the outer chamber. I'll venture there only if "
"desperate. Perhaps other researchers will open the doors before I reach that "
"point."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-858
msgctxt "51188213-0-858"
msgid "Dwarven Ruin Explorer's Journal"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-841
msgctxt "21337012-0-841"
msgid ""
"by Valrendil of the Crystal Tower, Research-Appointee to the Thalmor\n"
"\n"
"I shall endeavor to shed light on these most mysterious creatures, the "
"Argonians, paying particular attention to their mating rituals.\n"
"\n"
"Many speak in whispers of the Hist, a faceless entity with whom all "
"Argonians claim bonds. According to legend, the Hist lives at the heart of "
"Black Marsh in a tree that routinely walks the lands, patrolling its borders."
"\n"
"\n"
"Some say the wandering Hist is a metaphor for the Argonian condition. Doomed "
"to toil amongst the fetid swamps, they desire a way out of their misery. "
"Somehow the Argonians continue to survive, their numbers neither rising nor "
"falling regardless of adversity.\n"
"\n"
"The lizard-folk view mating as a simple call to procreation by their leader, "
"the Hist. To participate in this annual event, Argonians travel to the town "
"of Hissmir and engage in several trials. The trial winners are allowed to "
"mate, while losers must return the following year.\n"
"\n"
"Though I was unable to observe this year's trials, I hope to attend next "
"year in order to learn more about these strange and sub-Elven reptilians."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-841
msgctxt "51188213-0-841"
msgid "The Argonian Mating Ritual"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-69
msgctxt "21337012-0-69"
msgid ""
"Memorandum on Mnemic Acquisition\n"
"\n"
"Initial experiments uncovered a formula to duplicate the mnemic phenomenon. "
"We've yet to replicate the processes utilized by a \"\"Tree-Minder,\"\" yet "
"our solution is both elegant and thorough.\n"
"\n"
"The Hist sap proves to be an invaluable by-product. I hope to bring many "
"specimens back to the Crystal Tower to further research possible uses.\n"
"\n"
"Most Argonian subjects prove uncooperative, but we've had some success using "
"the extractions from the Hist as a crude form of coercive.\n"
"\n"
"This warrants a full investigation, one which I will personally oversee.\n"
"\n"
"— Alchemist <<1>>"
msgstr ""
"Mnemic 습득에 대한 보고서\n"
"\n"
"최초의 실험에서는 mnemic 현상을 재현하는 방법을 알아내지 못했다. 아직 \\\\\"\\\\\"나무 지킴이\\\\\"\\\\\"가 "
"이용하는 과정을 재현하지는 못했지만 우리의 해결책은 품격있고 완벽하다.\n"
"\n"
"히스트의 수액은 매우 귀중한 부산물로 정평이 나 있다. 수정탑으로 많은 양을 가져가서 사용법을 알아내면 좋겠는데.\n"
"\n"
"아르고니안 피실험자 대부분은 비협조적이지만, 히스트 원액을 강제적으로 추출하는 데 성공한 적도 몇 번 있다.\n"
"\n"
"확실히 상세한 조사가 필요하다. 내가 직접 감독해야겠다.\n"
"\n"
"— 연금술사 <<1>>"

#: 51188213-0-69
msgctxt "51188213-0-69"
msgid "Ruuvitar's Journal"
msgstr "Ruuvitar의 일지"

#: 21337012-0-628
msgctxt "21337012-0-628"
msgid ""
"I think Kireth and I may have discovered what we need to finally prove "
"ourselves to the Arch-Mage at the Academy of Shad Astula. The Dwemer ruins "
"of northern Tamriel hold amazing treasures of the lost Dwarves, but these "
"places are often too dangerous to navigate. I have discovered several "
"references in old texts to a method for controlling Dwemer constructs "
"through the use of a harmonic device that interacts with the constructs' "
"resonators. It'll take some time, and no small effort, but I think I can "
"actually build a prototype of the device to test.\n"
"\n"
"I truly am a genius. But I already knew that."
msgstr ""
"내 생각엔 키레스와 내가 마침내 샤드 아스툴라 아카데미의  대마법사에게 인정받기 위해 필요한 것을 발견한 것 같다.북부 탐리엘의 드웨머 "
"유적지는 사라진 드웨머들의 놀라운 보물을 품고있지만, 이 장소들은 종종 탐험하기엔 너무 위험해진다.나는 드웨머 구조물의 공명기와 "
"상호작용하는 조화 장치를 이용해 드웨머 구조물을 조종하는 방법을, 오래된 문서에 있는 몇 개의 참고문헌에서 발견했다. 시간과 노력이 "
"들겠지만 테스트를 위한 원형을 만들 수 있을 것 같다.\n"
"\n"
"난 진짜 천재다. 알고 있었지만."

#: 51188213-0-628
msgctxt "51188213-0-628"
msgid "Raynor's Journal: Bthanual"
msgstr "레이노어의 일지:브타누알"

#: 21337012-0-611
msgctxt "21337012-0-611"
msgid ""
"I should never have listened to Ameelus. He said the mire wasps can be tamed."
" He even claimed that a lightweight harness, made of string, can be used on "
"them. \n"
"\n"
"You would think I would have learned my lesson after the \"\"coat your "
"scales in scrib jelly to avoid getting burns\"\" fiasco, which was his last "
"brilliant idea.\n"
"\n"
"For future reference, covering your hands with honey and trying to coax "
"wasps into some degree of calmness doesn't work, either. And their stings "
"hurt. What a waste of a good jar of honey."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-611
msgctxt "51188213-0-611"
msgid "Wasp Wrangling"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-522
msgctxt "21337012-0-522"
msgid ""
"I've arrived at Ezduiin. I'm still nursing the wounds inflicted by Telenger. "
"And that faithless Andewen. I was certain we would spend the centuries "
"together, she and I. All she had to do was acknowledge my power—and "
"recognize that Telenger's time is past. \n"
"\n"
"- - -\n"
"I've explored the surface ruins, and found my way past the ancient magics "
"protecting the ruin's entrance. I have the undercroft to myself. The spirits "
"here seem to pay me no mind. So far.\n"
"\n"
"- - -\n"
"I've found it. The Mallari-Mora was lying just where it had fallen, all "
"those hundreds of years ago. I have nothing but time now. To discover the "
"secrets of Essanyon and plumb the heights of Aetherius.\n"
"\n"
"- - -\n"
"I've encountered a setback. In manipulating the magical energies surrounding "
"the relic, I seem to have rekindled a connection long dormant. The spirits "
"of Aetherius now flood the ruin. The dead bound by Essanyon's ritual once "
"again walk the stones of Ezduiin.\n"
"\n"
"- - -\n"
"I have mastered the Mallari-Mora. The enclosed sketches show how its "
"multifaceted sides can focus and purify magicka. While I have yet to muster "
"full control of the Aetherius shard coterminous with this ruin, I do have "
"rudimentary control over the spirits I've summoned. I now have guardians and "
"willing slaves.\n"
"\n"
"- - -\n"
"Telenger has arrived. I've sent the spirits to be my eyes. Andewen is with "
"him. This is it. Like misunderstood Essanyon before me, my time has come. "
"I'll take some of his pathetic students, swing wide the gates of Aetherius, "
"and claim my rightful place as arch-mage!"
msgstr ""
"에즈두인에 도착했다. 아직도 텔렌저에게 입은 상처를 다스리고 있다. 그리고 그 신의없는 안데웬에게 입은 상처도. 그녀와 나, 우리는 분명 "
"한 세기를 함께 보낼 수 있었을 텐데. 그녀는 나의 힘을 인정하고 텔렌저의 시간이 지나갔다는 사실을 깨닫기만 하면 되었단 말이다.\n"
"\n"
"- - -\n"
"유적지 표면을 탐사했고, 유적의 입구를 보호하고 있던 고대의 마법을 헤치고 나아갔다. 나는 내 스스로의 힘으로 지하실에 들어왔다. 여기 "
"있는 영혼들은 나를 신경쓰지 않는 것 같다. 지금까지는.\n"
"\n"
"- - -\n"
"내가 찾아냈다. 말라리-모라는 수 백년 전에 떨어졌던 바로 그 자리에 놓여 있었다. 지금 나에게 있는 것은 시간 뿐이다. 에사니온의 "
"비밀을 밝혀내고 에테리우스의 높이를 헤아릴 시간 말이다.\n"
"\n"
"- - -\n"
"차질이 생겼다. 내가 유물을 둘러싼 마법의 기운을 조정했을 때, 오랫동안 잠들어 있었던 연결을 다시 불러일으킨 모양이다. 지금 "
"에테리우스의 영혼들이 유적에 몰려들고 있다. 에사니온의 의식에 속박당한 망자들이 다시 한번 에즈두인의 돌 위를 걸어다닌다.\n"
"\n"
"- - -\n"
"말라리-모라에 통달했다. 동봉되어 있던 밑그림을 보고 그 다면적인 면들이 어떻게 매지카를 집중시키고 정화할 수 있는지 알 수 있었다. "
"아직 이 유적과 매우 유사한 에테리우스 조각을 완전히 통제하지는 못했지만, 내가 소환해낸 영혼들에 대한 기본적인 통제권을 가질 수 있었다."
" 나는 이제 수호자이자 순종적인 노예들을 얻은 것이다.\n"
"\n"
"- - -\n"
"텔렌저가 도착했다. 영혼들을 보내어 내 눈으로 삼았다. 안데웬도 놈과 함께 있었다. 이제 시작이다. 내 이전에 제대로 인정받지 못했던 "
"에사니온처럼, 나의 시간이 온 것이다. 놈의 한심한 학생들을 몇 명 붙잡아서, 에테리우스의 관문을 활짝 열어내고, 대마법사로서의 내 "
"정당한 지위를 요구할 것이다!"

#: 51188213-0-522
msgctxt "51188213-0-522"
msgid "Uricantar's Journal"
msgstr "우리칸타의 일지"

#: 21337012-0-5088
msgctxt "21337012-0-5088"
msgid ""
"The most recent formula is nothing short of a miraculous success. When "
"administered to young healthy gryphons and those in the early stages of the "
"disease, the results are total remission of symptoms and full recovery. "
"Although most developing gryphons in the advanced stages of the disease are "
"driven from the nest and eaten by welwas, those that survive can also be "
"treated. Though their wings may need to be amputated, their wounds will no "
"longer suffer from chronic infection, so the creatures may live out "
"comfortable lives in captivity.\n"
"\n"
"With your approval, Conservator, we may begin manufacture and distribution "
"of the wing rot cure to our rangers and administer it to gryphons in the "
"wild."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-5088
msgctxt "51188213-0-5088"
msgid "Report on Wing Rot Curative Trials"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-5087
msgctxt "21337012-0-5087"
msgid ""
"I recently attempted to imbue a fellrunner with wisp essence and observed a "
"rather curious reaction. Within a few seconds of the applied reagent, the "
"creature simply dropped dead. Nothing out of the ordinary you might think, "
"but upon closer observation the bird's carcass was gently steaming and the "
"air was filled with a surprisingly mouthwatering aroma. Dissection revealed "
"that the bird had been cooked from within, to perfection I might add. "
"Conservator Vinelore seemed unimpressed by these results, but I want to "
"attempt to recreate them in more easily available fauna."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-5087
msgctxt "51188213-0-5087"
msgid "Fellrunner Failure?"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-5086
msgctxt "21337012-0-5086"
msgid ""
"Our experiments to enhance the abilities of imps have, universally, resulted "
"in disastrous side effects, though this latest round of testing is perhaps "
"the most spectacular example. When applying a serum concocted from the "
"essence of an imp with affinity to frost to an imp with an affinity for fire "
"the end result is not a creature with mastery over both, but a puddle. The "
"unfortunate thing melted before our eyes, shrieking at ear splitting volumes "
"until its throat collapsed. Or perhaps its lungs. Either way we wont be "
"repeating that particular experiment again."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-5086
msgctxt "51188213-0-5086"
msgid "Findings on the Elemental Volatility of Imps"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-460
msgctxt "21337012-0-460"
msgid ""
"We've reached an impasse. A room of doors. Every door we've tried seems to "
"return back to the entrance. There must some clues in these ancient runes.\n"
"\n"
"- - - \n"
"Two weeks and still blocked by the doors. Kireth thinks we're a day away, "
"but she's been saying that for a week.\n"
"\n"
"- - - \n"
"A Companion patrol showed up late last night, talking about the Worm Cult. "
"We haven't seen a robe yet, but … we'll post guards. Keep watch. At least "
"the big one is keeping Kireth motivated.\n"
"\n"
"- - - \n"
"We've done it. My damned sister is a genius.  She translated the runes:\n"
"\n"
"\"\"Deep sea swimmer. Surfaces on the clear day. Far overhead, eyes watch. "
"Watch on the wing. Far below, scales rasp. The venom pulses. All are as one "
"in the sight of our lord Alduin.\"\""
msgstr ""
"우리는 문 앞의 방에서 교착 상태에 빠졌다. 우리가 시도했던 모든 문은 입구까지 다시 돌아오는 것 같다. 이 고대 유적에 몇 가지 단서가 "
"있을 것이다.\n"
"\n"
"- - - \n"
"2주째인데 아직도 문 옆에 가로막혀 있다. 키레스는 우리가 하루 밖에 없다고 생각하지만, 그녀는 일주일째 그렇게 말하고 있다.\n"
"\n"
"- - - \n"
"어젯밤 늦게 컴패니언 순찰대가 벌레 교단 얘기를 하며 나타났다. 아직 로브입은 놈을 못 봤지만... 경비원을 배치해 잘 지켜야 한다. "
"적어도 키레스가 동기부여는 받겠지.\n"
"\n"
"- - - \n"
"우리가 해냈어. 내 여동생은 천재다. 그녀는 룬문자를 번역했다.\n"
"\n"
"\\\\\"\\\\\"깊은 바다를 헤엄치는 자. 맑은 날의 표면.머리 위 먼 곳에서 지켜보는 눈. 날개를 보라. 저 아래에서는 비늘이 "
"울린다. 독이 진동한다 우리의 알두인께서는 모든 것을 하나로 보신다.'"

#: 51188213-0-460
msgctxt "51188213-0-460"
msgid "Delver Notes"
msgstr "탐험가의 기록문서"

#: 21337012-0-428
msgctxt "21337012-0-428"
msgid ""
"Been reading \"\"The Art of Love and Swordplay\"\" by the bard Fjokki. I "
"don't get it. Why is this stupid book so popular?\n"
"\n"
"I'm pretty sure half of the things described aren't even possible. Or legal. "
"Oh, wait a minute—this one sounds kind of interesting."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-428
msgctxt "51188213-0-428"
msgid "Kireth's Journal, Page 33"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-427
msgctxt "21337012-0-427"
msgid ""
"Had a few too many close calls trying to salvage some metal to make new "
"lockpicks. I'm not terribly interested in getting impaled on a spike. And "
"every time I stop to dig around for the key, the constructs swarm after me.\n"
"\n"
"I'll need to invent something protective when I manage to get out of here. "
"Maybe some kind of special boots. Or a hat."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-427
msgctxt "51188213-0-427"
msgid "Kireth's Journal, Page 30"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-426
msgctxt "21337012-0-426"
msgid ""
"The lock on the Dwemer mechanism is far more complex than any I've dealt "
"with before.\n"
"\n"
"All of my lockpicks have snapped. \n"
"\n"
"Note to Self: Find some Dwemer metal I can use to craft new lockpicks.\n"
"\n"
"Note to Raynor: Stop letting me get myself into these predicaments!"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-426
msgctxt "51188213-0-426"
msgid "Kireth's Journal, Page 29"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-425
msgctxt "21337012-0-425"
msgid ""
"Oh, this isn't good. Not good at all. The constructs seem to know I'm here "
"and they keep looking for me. Where's my useless brother when I really need "
"him?\n"
"\n"
"I hope someone comes looking for me soon. I can't get out of here without "
"attracting more constructs. And now I'm hungry.\n"
"\n"
"This is bad! This is worse than when Raynor built that thing that turned all "
"the clothes in town invisible for a day and a half. Vivec, was Elder Aro mad "
"about that!"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-425
msgctxt "51188213-0-425"
msgid "Kireth's Journal, Page 25"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-424
msgctxt "21337012-0-424"
msgid ""
"Someone else has been in here, and I'm not talking about the ancient "
"Dwarves! I found a bridge, obviously not of Dwemer origin, and I see "
"numerous signs that other explorers recently visited this ruin.\n"
"\n"
"I wonder what they found? They better not have taken all the best stuff!\n"
"\n"
"Wait a moment. What if they weren't as fast and clever as me? What if a trap "
"or a construct got them?\n"
"\n"
"I really don't want to come across their horribly mutilated bodies. That "
"would be gross."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-424
msgctxt "51188213-0-424"
msgid "Kireth's Journal, Page 16"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-423
msgctxt "21337012-0-423"
msgid ""
"I wish I could spend more time in here. I see evidence of some kind of "
"massive machine, but I don't have time to pry open all the doors and look "
"for it.\n"
"\n"
"Stupid journal binding! Why do my pages keep falling out?\n"
"\n"
"You know, it's a pain locating these ancient ruins. They're always in the "
"most inconvenient places.\n"
"\n"
"Once you find them, though, exploring is so worth the effort. I'd give up "
"the Mages Guild entirely if I knew where all the ruins were. Then I could "
"spend all my time exploring."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-423
msgctxt "51188213-0-423"
msgid "Kireth's Journal, Page 10"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-4117
msgctxt "21337012-0-4117"
msgid ""
"Ash Yam: No effect. Kwama will eat it if they are peckish.\n"
"\n"
"Bittergreen: No effect. Empty Bittergreen pods are attractive sitting "
"locations for workers and scribs. I've seen warriors attempt to enter the "
"pods when they obviously can't fit. Stupid bugs. Keep these out of the mine.\n"
"\n"
"Black Anther: No effect on the kwama, and we have to send operatives near "
"Vivec City to find it, which is risky. Suggested to cease testing.\n"
"\n"
"Black Lichen: The kwama hate it. Use it only to keep them out of spaces we "
"don't want them to be near, like our food stores.\n"
"\n"
"Bungler's Bane: No effect and hard to find in reasonable supply.\n"
"\n"
"Chokeweed: No effect.\n"
"\n"
"Comberry: No effect and extremely hard to find in the wild. If we need more "
"it's recommended to steal some from the merchants in Vivec City.\n"
"\n"
"Corkbulb Root: Not the effect we are looking for, although it seems useful "
"for treating kwama with any form of paralysis. Continued testing is "
"recommended.\n"
"\n"
"Draggle-tail: None in supply and it's not yet worth sending scouts to the "
"Bitter Coast.\n"
"\n"
"Fire Fern: Kwama love this stuff, while at the same time it appears to make "
"them agitated. More research on this is recommended.\n"
"\n"
"Gold Kanet: No effect.\n"
"\n"
"Green Lichen: Can't find it anywhere. Every recommended location has so far "
"turned out to be a dead end.\n"
"\n"
"Hackle-Lo: No effect.\n"
"\n"
"Heather: No effect.\n"
"\n"
"Kresh Fiber: Kwama hate it, and not in the way we're interested in. They "
"defecate on it as soon as it's discovered. Keep all supply out of Matus-Akin."
"\n"
"\n"
"Luminous Russula: Grows naturally around the area and can be found in the "
"mine as well. Kwama consume it often. No obvious effects on behavior.\n"
"\n"
"Marshmerrow: No effect aside from potential feed.\n"
"\n"
"Muck: Toxic to Kwama. DO NOT USE!\n"
"\n"
"Nirnroot: Do not use on its own anywhere near the kwama. It appears to make "
"them lethargic, yet they crave it once exposed. We had to put a few warriors "
"down after the primary exposure. We don't want to lose any more, as there "
"are not many of these beasts to begin with.\n"
"\n"
"Red Lichen: No effect.\n"
"\n"
"Roobrush: No effect.\n"
"\n"
"Saltrice: Common kwama feed. We keep a supply of this in the storage area "
"surrounded by a moderate amount of Black Lichen.\n"
"\n"
"Scathecraw: No effect.\n"
"\n"
"Slough Fern: No effect.\n"
"\n"
"Stoneflower: Only found in the West Gash. Too risky to acquire. I speculate "
"it will have no effect regardless.\n"
"\n"
"Trama Root: No effect.\n"
"\n"
"Violet Coprinus: We have found this growing naturally in Matus-Akin. "
"Potential natural kwama feed. No effect.\n"
"\n"
"Wickwheat: Makes kwama even stupider than they already are. More research "
"needed. \n"
"\n"
"Willow Flower: No effect.\n"
"\n"
"Hypha Facia: Sometimes Found in Matus-Akin, no obvious effect."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-4117
msgctxt "51188213-0-4117"
msgid "Kwama Breeding Research Notes (Flora)"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-4033
msgctxt "21337012-0-4033"
msgid ""
"One thing has been gnawing at me that I dare not share with the masters. "
"Dare not share with anyone. The true source of the formula. It seemed too "
"arcane, too brilliant for even a great alchemist to develop. Not that I "
"couldn't likely produce something similar given enough time and resources, "
"but my method, my language, would never be so … flawless. Even I can admit "
"that.\n"
"\n"
"I found the answer. It was staring at me all this time in the middle of the "
"shrine. Clavicus Vile. A maker of deals, granter of wishes, and not one I "
"would ever wish to be indebted to.\n"
"\n"
"It seems this ruin was stumbled upon once before in a very similar fashion "
"to how we found it. It is likely they were the previous owners of Vassir-"
"Didanat mine. It's a well-kept secret that the mine is not particularly rich."
" It produces barely enough ebony to make it worth working at all. And these "
"mer that came before us grew desperate. They called out to Vile.\n"
"\n"
"A particular lack of wisdom and foresight it was that made them wish for an "
"endless source of ebony. One must choose words carefully when dealing with "
"Daedra. Although in this case it may have been better to make no deal at all."
" Regardless, some pact was made and the formula came to them. They must have "
"successfully brewed it, for we found statues here dating back centuries. But "
"suspiciously they kept very little records about their progress, or how they "
"used it. \n"
"\n"
"In truth, knowing this fact makes me somewhat uneasy. Sometimes I feel like "
"I can hear the statue of Clavicus Vile whispering, or laughing softly to "
"itself. But I made no deal with him. I am simply studying the result. He "
"holds no sway over me."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-4033
msgctxt "51188213-0-4033"
msgid "The Source of the Formula"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-388
msgctxt "21337012-0-388"
msgid ""
"Raynor will be so proud of me! I documented my entire exploration of the "
"ruins (even though this stupid journal keeps falling apart) and I found the "
"Dwemer vault.\n"
"\n"
"But without Raynor's device, how will I avoid the constructs to find the "
"key? Danger is only fun to boast about later."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-388
msgctxt "51188213-0-388"
msgid "Kireth's Journal, Page 24"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-387
msgctxt "21337012-0-387"
msgid ""
"I found it! I'm sure this is the vault where the Dwemer kept all their best "
"lore and stuff. There was even this weird crystal mechanism, but I need a "
"key to activate it.\n"
"\n"
"And now this stupid device that Raynor gave me is really starting to act up. "
"I don't think it's going to last long enough to get me past these constructs."
" I'd better find a place to hide until I can figure out what to do next."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-387
msgctxt "51188213-0-387"
msgid "Kireth's Journal, Page 22"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-386
msgctxt "21337012-0-386"
msgid ""
"Curse the luck! Stupid, cheap journal binding! Some of my best entries have "
"fallen out! Oh, well.\n"
"\n"
"This whole place rumbles every so often. As I get deeper into the ruins, "
"Mzulft feels more and more unstable. It's like the entire structure is about "
"to collapse or something. That would be bad.\n"
"\n"
"I came across spots where the walls and ceiling have fallen in, letting in "
"snow and sunshine. And I feel a cold breeze blowing from deeper in. I hope "
"the passage I'm looking for isn't buried.\n"
"\n"
"Damn! The wind took another page!"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-386
msgctxt "51188213-0-386"
msgid "Kireth's Journal, Page 19"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-385
msgctxt "21337012-0-385"
msgid ""
"A lot of Mzulft is pristine. It's abandoned, like all of the Dwemer ruins "
"we've explored. And it's empty, except for the constructs. But everything "
"still works. It's eerie to see glowing lights on the wall and hear the pipes "
"steaming. It's like the place is waiting for someone, like the occupants "
"just stepped out and will return at any moment.\n"
"\n"
"I wish I could just explore these ruins. Every ruin tells another story, and "
"if I don't get to crawl into every corner, that story is just half-told. "
"Raynor would laugh if he heard me say that. You'd better not read this, "
"brother!"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-385
msgctxt "51188213-0-385"
msgid "Kireth's Journal, Page 14"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-384
msgctxt "21337012-0-384"
msgid ""
"Raynor's magic device works pretty well. I'm practically invisible to "
"Dwarven constructs. It does flicker every three and a half minutes, though. "
"I've got to make sure nothing's nearby when I finish counting to two hundred "
"and ten.\n"
"\n"
"I had a few close calls before I determined the time between each misfire, "
"but since I figured that out I haven't had any problems.\n"
"\n"
"Raynor got the idea for this device while studying the light crystals at "
"Bthanual. Amazing—one of his devices actually serves a useful purpose!"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-384
msgctxt "51188213-0-384"
msgid "Kireth's Journal, Page 12"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-383
msgctxt "21337012-0-383"
msgid ""
"This place is full of traps! I've never seen so many interesting or "
"dangerous contraptions in one place. I wonder what the Dwarves were hiding "
"in here that needed so much protection? I'll wager that whatever it is, it "
"would certainly impress those stuffed robes in the Guild.\n"
"\n"
"There are so many locked doors and passageways. I wish I could explore them "
"all! But one thing at a time. Raynor says I have a tendency to "
"overcomplicate things. Like he should talk!"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-383
msgctxt "51188213-0-383"
msgid "Kireth's Journal, Page 7"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-382
msgctxt "21337012-0-382"
msgid ""
"Raynor and I are actually getting paid for this delve! That's a step up, as "
"far as I'm concerned.\n"
"\n"
"After Bthanual, who needs the Academy? We're ready for the big time! Bring "
"on the Mages Guild!\n"
"\n"
"But we really need to find something good to impress the Guild. Sometimes it "
"feels like they're just humoring us.\n"
"\n"
"Raynor thinks that with the backing of the King of Skyrim, though, we have a "
"better chance to get in. I hope he's right."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-382
msgctxt "51188213-0-382"
msgid "Kireth's Journal, Page 3"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-381
msgctxt "21337012-0-381"
msgid ""
"3rd Sun's Dawn, 2E 129\n"
"\n"
"Assuming I'm interpreting these scrolls correctly, this orb, when magically "
"charged, retains images within its cloudy depths. The scrolls depict it "
"containing information on two specific topics: the use of Dwemer soul gems "
"and maps of Dwemer installations.\n"
"\n"
"Obviously, the mage-scholars will want the information about soul gems, but "
"the maps are more interesting to me. As-yet-unearthed Dwemer ruins may "
"contain much more valuable knowledge, although the mages would balk at "
"passing on practical information that can be used right now. There's a "
"lecture on the relative value of a bird-in-the-hand in my immediate future.\n"
"\n"
"Imprinting an orb appears simple. I just need to hold one near one of these "
"Dwemer memory devices (the ones with the crystals) and the energy will rush "
"into it, along with the associated information. But I'd need to find an orb "
"to copy the information to. That's more of an issue. All I've found are "
"glass shards, and the few intact orbs I've found have been smashed in "
"altercations with the constructs. They seem to want to destroy the orbs "
"rather than let me have one.\n"
"\n"
"Wait a moment. Something's happening. Why are the vault doors closing?\n"
"\n"
"4th Sun's Dawn, 2E 129\n"
"\n"
"I'm estimating on the time. It's probably the next day by now. The vault "
"doors have closed behind me, and are quite thoroughly locked. I'll have to "
"come up with a different way to escape. I did find an intact orb in the "
"sacks here, but I'm going to wait to use it until I'm sure I can get out of "
"here."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-381
msgctxt "51188213-0-381"
msgid "Mzulft Researcher's Journal"
