#: 21337012-0-325
msgctxt "21337012-0-325"
msgid ""
"Sorry if these notes are a little disorganized, professor. I didn't want to "
"trim anything out that you might find useful.\n"
"\n"
"— Two distinct species: land dreugh and water dreugh.\n"
"\n"
"— Both were once common throughout Vvardenfell, Ebonheart, and the "
"surrounding waters. They've been driven out over the last few centuries and "
"only exist now in isolated pockets.\n"
"\n"
"— Some accounts assert there are two varieties of land dreugh, while others "
"maintain these are but the male and female versions of one kind of creature.\n"
"\n"
"— Legends tell of \"\"civilized\"\" land dreugh colonies which supposedly "
"raised herds of mudcrabs as food stock.\n"
"\n"
"— These colonies were also purported to have built stone cairn houses and "
"structures.\n"
"\n"
"— No evidence of such advanced dreugh behavior exists today.\n"
"\n"
"— Dreugh are omnivores and have been witnessed consuming mer flesh.\n"
"\n"
"— Dreugh are capable of channeling some form of shock energy through their "
"bodies. Most scholars agree this is a natural adaptation and not magical in "
"nature.\n"
"\n"
"— The land dreugh carapace is naturally sturdy and can deflect most attacks "
"from common weapons.\n"
"\n"
"— No known language or communication abilities.\n"
"\n"
"— Nesting habits are not well-documented, but we do know the land dreugh "
"encase their egg broods in mud. Nothing is known about water dreugh nesting "
"or egg-laying behavior.\n"
"\n"
"— Some fisherfolk are known to gather land dreugh eggs from the creatures' "
"mud-nests, though it is obviously a rather dangerous occupation.\n"
"\n"
"If this is enough information, I'll begin the netch research tomorrow."
msgstr ""
"내용이 좀 뒤죽박죽이라 죄송합니다, 교수님. 교수님께 유용할 지도 모르는 정보들을 임의로 다듬지 않으려고 했습니다.\n"
"\n"
"— 두 가지 다른 종류: 육지 드레그와 수생 드레그.\n"
"\n"
"— 둘 다 한때 바덴펠, 에본하트 전역 및 그 연안에 널리 분포했었음. 지난 몇 세기 동안 그들을 몰아낸 결과, 이제는 일부 고립된 "
"지역에만 존재함.\n"
"\n"
"— 어떤 이야기에선 두 가지 종류의 육지 드레그가 존재한다고 주장하나, 한편에선 같은 종류 생물의 암수 차이일 뿐이라고도 함.\n"
"\n"
"— ‘문명화된’ 육지 드레그들이 아마 진흙게들을 식용 가축으로 길렀을 것이라고 하는 이야기가 전해짐.\n"
"\n"
"— 이런 드레그 사회에서는 돌을 쌓아 집과 건축물을 지었다고 함.\n"
"\n"
"— 오늘날 드레그에게 그러한 진보된 행동양식은 관찰되지 않음.\n"
"\n"
"— 드레그는 잡식성으로, 머를 먹는 것이 목격된 적이 있음.\n"
"\n"
"— 드레그는 일종의 전기 에너지를 몸에 흐르게 할 수 있음. 대부분의 학자들은 이것이 자연적인 적응의 결과이지 마법적 성질의 것은 "
"아니라고 함.\n"
"\n"
"— 육지 드레그의 갑각은 견고하여 일반적인 무기 공격을 튕겨낼 수 있음.\n"
"\n"
"— 언어나 의사소통 능력에 대해서는 알려지지 않음.\n"
"\n"
"— 둥지를 짓는 습성에 대해서는 제대로 기록된 바가 없으나, 육지 드레그들이 알들을 진흙으로 둘러싸는 것은 익히 알려짐. 수생 드레그의 "
"둥지나 알 낳는 습성에 대해서는 알려진 바가 없음.\n"
"\n"
"— 몇몇 어업인들이 진흙 둥지에서 육지 드레그의 알을 채집한다고 하는데, 아주 위험한 일이 아닐 수 없음.\n"
"\n"
"이걸로 충분하다면 내일부터는 네치에 대해 조사하도록 하겠습니다."

#: 51188213-0-325
msgctxt "51188213-0-325"
msgid "Notes on the Dreugh"
msgstr "드레그에 대하여"

#: 21337012-0-2937
msgctxt "21337012-0-2937"
msgid ""
"2nd Sun's Dawn \n"
"\n"
"The kwama have grown agitated in recent weeks. Peculiar, considering it's "
"been months since they became accustomed to my scent, as they have with the "
"miners'.\n"
"\n"
"10th Sun's Dawn\n"
"\n"
"The miners and I found the corpse of a thunderbug this morning, along with "
"the bodies of perhaps a dozen warrior kwama. We're uncertain what path the "
"thunderbug took to get here, but we'll find it—this mine will not survive a "
"full invasion."
msgstr ""
"여명 2일\n"
"\n"
"요 몇 주 동안 크와마들이 점점 더 불안해하고 있다. 광부 크와마들이 내 냄새에 익숙해진지도 몇 달이 되었다는 사실을 생각해 보면 이상한 "
"일이다.\n"
"\n"
"여명 10일\n"
"\n"
"오늘 아침에 광부 크와마들과 내가 전사 크와마 십여 마리와 함께 나뒹굴고 있는 천둥벌레 시체를 찾아냈다. 천둥벌레가 어떤 경로를 통해서 "
"여기까지 들어왔는지는 불확실하지만, 그 길을 찾아내야 한다. 완전한 침략을 받는다면 이 광산은 살아남지 못할 것이다."

#: 51188213-0-2937
msgctxt "51188213-0-2937"
msgid "Nimriell's Research"
msgstr "님리엘의 연구 기록"

#: 21337012-0-2556
msgctxt "21337012-0-2556"
msgid ""
"or, A Defense Against the Planemeld\n"
"\n"
"Unnatural anchors blight the skies of Tamriel. Those learned in such matters "
"know they herald the Planemeld, a Daedric plot of unfathomable darkness.\n"
"\n"
"But in times when all hope seems lost, the Eight Divines provide. We can "
"salvage our future by looking to the past. <<A:1>> is our first bulwark "
"against Molag Bal's devious plot!\n"
"\n"
"The peculiar construction of this Ayleid ruin should be immediately apparent "
"to a scholar of the Eight Divines. The symmetrical nature of its "
"construction, the altar plate below the eight-tined arch, and the harmonic "
"blending of tonal triptychs reveal the divine hand in its formation. Should "
"one blow a large enough horn within the chancel's walls, its clarion call "
"would be heard as far as <<2>>!\n"
"\n"
"After extensive research, I believe this to be one piece of the long-rumored "
"Octal Cage. There should be seven ruins identical to this scattered "
"throughout Tamriel. Where, I do not know, but I shall locate them all. Then "
"I will find the eight Hallowed Clarions mentioned in the apocryphal accounts "
"of the Ayleid loss of Sancre Tor to Alessia.\n"
"\n"
"A daunting task, but the Octal Cage was thought capable of sealing the "
"Daedric Princes away from Nirn for good. Sounding a Hallowed Clarion in all "
"eight ruins, all at the same time, may be enough to bring the Octal Cage to "
"life.\n"
"\n"
"I depart in the morning. If my task proves fruitless, so be it. We must all "
"oppose the Harvester of Souls as best we can. Until then, any who calls the "
"God of Schemes their enemy may avail themselves of my laboratory."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2556
msgctxt "51188213-0-2556"
msgid "Closing the Octal Cage"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-2510
msgctxt "21337012-0-2510"
msgid ""
"by Hatiha\n"
"\n"
"One must be wary of the desert lizards. Two are poisonous, one eats only "
"live flesh, but the rest are safe.\n"
"\n"
"This one has found it nearly impossible to tell one from the other by their "
"looks. Only by learning their individual attributes can one be sure of the "
"lizard one has in hand.\n"
"\n"
"They can be tamed with patience. Approach carefully, and offer small bugs "
"(watch for the flesh-eater). As they become used to your scent, they will "
"learn to obey."
msgstr ""
"하티하 씀\n"
"\n"
"사막의 도마뱀을 조심해야 한다. 둘은 독성이 있고, 하나는 살아있는 고기만을 먹는다. 하지만 나머지는 안전하다.\n"
"\n"
"이 카짓은 도마뱀의 생김새만 봐서는 그 두 부류를 구별하기가 거의 불가능하다는 것을 알게 되었다. 녀석들 개개의 특성을 배워야만 도마뱀을 "
"확실하게 손에 넣을 수 있다.\n"
"\n"
"도마뱀을 길들이려면 인내심을 가져야 한다. 조심스럽게 접근하고 작은 벌레를 제공해라(육식을 하는 녀석을 기다려라). 녀석들이 당신의 "
"냄새에 익숙해지면 순종하는 법을 배울 것이다."

#: 51188213-0-2510
msgctxt "51188213-0-2510"
msgid "Lizards"
msgstr "도마뱀들"

#: 21337012-0-2467
msgctxt "21337012-0-2467"
msgid ""
"Verandis and his thirst for knowledge and research is going to be the death "
"of me. Watching a big, dumb spider is just plain boring!\n"
"\n"
"Big spider tended eggs.\n"
"\n"
"Big spider spun webs.\n"
"\n"
"Big spider bored me, so I'm done here.\n"
"\n"
"—Gwendis"
msgstr ""
"베란디스와 그의 지식, 연구에 대한 갈망 때문에 죽을 지경이다. 거대하고 멍청한 거미를 지켜보는 일은 너무 지루하단 말이야!\n"
"\n"
"거대 거미가 알을 낳았다.\n"
"\n"
"거대 거미가 거미줄을 쳤다.\n"
"\n"
"거대 거미가 날 지루하게 했다. 그러니 여기서 끝낸다.\n"
"\n"
"— 그웬디스"

#: 51188213-0-2467
msgctxt "51188213-0-2467"
msgid "Ravenwatch Research: Aesar Hatespinner"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-2466
msgctxt "21337012-0-2466"
msgid ""
"This may be the earliest of the Ayleid ruins that culminated in the Doomcrag."
"\n"
"\n"
"Even the place's name—Sea Journey's End—resonates with the history I have "
"pieced together. And the gift of magicka continues to inhabit this ancient "
"structure.\n"
"\n"
"—Verandis"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2466
msgctxt "51188213-0-2466"
msgid "Ravenwatch Research: Veawend Ede"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-2384
msgctxt "21337012-0-2384"
msgid ""
"The Llodos plague is a damn complex concoction. I'm not sure I have the "
"skill and experience to totally counteract its properties, but I have an "
"idea for how to suppress and slow the pace of the disease. It will require a "
"number of rare and exotic ingredients to pull this off, though.\n"
"\n"
"An alchemical concoction such as I'm imagining doesn't like to be subjected "
"to high heat. It's too volatile. It needs to be allowed to steep and brew. "
"Therefore, an adjustment of one-quarter flame should suffice to get the "
"alembic to the proper temperature.\n"
"\n"
"First, I'll need a good amount of Kyne's Heart. These healing herbs are "
"prized for their powerful medicinal properties, which makes them hard to "
"come by and extremely expensive. I'm certain the innkeeper at the Brooding "
"Elf keeps an emergency supply to sell for profit when business gets slow.\n"
"\n"
"Then, I need something to bind it all together and hide the foul taste of "
"the bitter herbs. Something like sour milk tea. Grell Flan was known to "
"imbibe the stuff from time to time. I must admit that I have a fondness for "
"the beverage myself. Usually with a splash of greef to give it a bit of a "
"kick, if you must know.\n"
"\n"
"Finally, I'll need something that adds a touch of magic. Dragon scale "
"mushrooms would fit the bill nicely. If I recall correctly, Old Sorel Tedas "
"had a taste for exotic mushrooms. There might still be some hidden in his "
"house—unless those Argonian ruffians ransacked his place after he entered "
"the quarantine."
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2384
msgctxt "51188213-0-2384"
msgid "Alchemist Nilyne's Notes"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-2374
msgctxt "21337012-0-2374"
msgid ""
"Ah, finally. Perfection! The latest batch of curative starts the affliction, "
"progresses the plague at a reasonable rate of speed, and then turns the "
"afflicted into plague husks seventy percent of the time. Now we have a "
"superior version of the plague and an effective way to dispense it.\n"
"\n"
"Of course, handing out curatives can be a slow process, especially in the "
"larger towns and cities. Before we begin operations in Mournhold, we'll need "
"a faster way to disperse the plague. But that's not my task at this moment. "
"Besides, I'm sure that Alchemist Merdyndril is tackling this problem even as "
"I write these notes.\n"
"\n"
"I should also record that I've perfected the husk scent. We can once again "
"walk among the husks without fear of being attacked. I might even have an "
"idea about a soap to remove the scent after we're finished.\n"
"\n"
"We'll begin making larger batches of the curative immediately. In no time at "
"all, we should be able to give everyone at the Serk and in the immediate "
"vicinity a dosage of the curative. Don't worry, my mistress. Everything will "
"happen, just as you have foreseen.\n"
"\n"
"—Nostrum Breva"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2374
msgctxt "51188213-0-2374"
msgid "Curative Batch Nineteen"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-2361
msgctxt "21337012-0-2361"
msgid ""
"This batch of the curative was so close to perfect. Unfortunately, it was a "
"tad too effective. The afflicted turned into violent husks far more quickly "
"than we had hoped for at this point in the process. Perhaps this particular "
"mixture will be useful later, when we need a quick influx of undead "
"soldiers, but for now this batch won't suffice.\n"
"\n"
"An interesting side effect of this version of the curative concerns the "
"level of aggressiveness demonstrated by the newly created husks. They turn "
"immediately violent and consider everything that moves to be an enemy. Or "
"food.\n"
"\n"
"These husks also demonstrated a total disregard for the husk scent we apply "
"when working in close proximity to them. They attacked our workers as soon "
"as they saw them, indicating that the scent no longer masks us from husks "
"created with this version of the curative.\n"
"\n"
"Let's increase the cooking time by one hour and decrease the amount of wolf "
"bile by twenty-five percent.\n"
"\n"
"—Nostrum Breva"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2361
msgctxt "51188213-0-2361"
msgid "Curative Batch Fifteen"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-2360
msgctxt "21337012-0-2360"
msgid ""
"Useless! Absolutely useless! The curative isn't going to meet our mistress's "
"demanding standards if it simply kills the person who ingests it! If we were "
"trying to create a new poison, then we'd be wildly successful. But that "
"isn't the task at hand.\n"
"\n"
"Reduce the amount of dried corpse blood and try again. And watch the "
"temperature in those cauldrons. One of them was dangerously close to boiling "
"over—and I for one have no desire to be drenched in a spray of boiling "
"curative.\n"
"\n"
"—Nostrum Breva"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2360
msgctxt "51188213-0-2360"
msgid "Curative Batch Six"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-2261
msgctxt "21337012-0-2261"
msgid ""
"|arPAGE 7\n"
"|alTRIAL 21:\n"
"ADJUSTMENT: No moisture\n"
"RESULTS: All crops died\n"
"NOTES: Plants seem to need moisture. Denying it caused withering and rapid "
"crop death.\n"
"\n"
"TRIAL 22:\n"
"ADJUSTMENT: Water alternative\n"
"RESULTS: Crops initially thrived, eventually died\n"
"NOTES: Animal urine employed as water alternative. Animals seemed to resent "
"being held in place until urination occurred. Cats were especially difficult."
" Badilia vocally resented having to restrain animals and being splashed with "
"urine. Had to pay bonus.\n"
"\n"
"TRIAL 23:\n"
"ADJUSTMENT: Add rocks\n"
"RESULTS: Crops failed to grow at all\n"
"NOTES: Badilia said that rocks around plants help hold in moisture. Planted "
"seeds and placed rocks on top. No crop growth noted at all. Suspect Badilia "
"of ill intent.\n"
"\n"
"TRIAL 24:\n"
"ADJUSTMENT: Add rocks, Part II\n"
"RESULTS: Crops thrived\n"
"NOTES: Badilia explained that rocks are applied after crops have sprouted. "
"Eye rolling and sighing was excessive. Waited until crops broke through the "
"ground, then placed rocks around stems. Success was noted. Badilia called it "
"\"\"keeping their feet wet\"\"; confusing, as plants do not have feet.\n"
"\n"
"TRIAL 25:\n"
"ADJUSTMENT: Constant moisture\n"
"RESULTS: Test not yet complete\n"
"NOTES: If some moisture is good for plants, then more must be better. Have "
"flooded fields and am keeping plants constantly wet. Eye rolling detected "
"from Badilia, but trial continues."
msgstr ""

