#: 21337012-0-2210
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "21337012-0-2210"
msgid ""
"Still recovering from prior incident with the device. Some adjustments need "
"to be made, obviously. More magicka is needed, much more, along with a "
"better method of forcefully channeling it into upward movement.\n"
"\n"
"And next time I hope to land in the water.\n"
"\n"
"Nothing great has ever been accomplished without setbacks and pain. And what "
"goal could be greater than this? They laughed when I shouted \"\"From Nirn "
"to the Aether … and back!\"\" from the rooftops, but I will have the last "
"chortle. It is more than a motto to me, it is my life's quest.\n"
"\n"
"It can be done and I will do it. Every trial takes me one step closer. "
"Tomorrow's attempt will be the breakthrough, I feel it in my bones. I sense "
"the stars aligning in favor of my quest. My name will be recorded in the "
"scrolls of history!"
msgstr ""
"이전의 사건으로 장비에서 복구 중. 일부 조정은 분명히 이루어져야합니다. 더 많은 magicka가 더 많이 필요합니다.\n"
"\n"
"그리고 물에 착륙하기를 희망하는 다음 시간.\n"
"\n"
"좌절과 고통없이 결코 위대한 일은 없습니다. 그리고 이보다 더 큰 목표가있을 수 있습니까? 그들은 Nirn에서 Aether까지 외쳤다. "
"웃었다. 옥상에서.하지만 나는 마지막 chortle을 가질 것이다. 그것은 내 삶의 모토입니다.\n"
"\n"
"할 수 있고 그것을 할 것입니다. 모든 재판을 통해 한 걸음 더 가깝습니다. 내일의 시도는 돌파구가 될 것입니다, 나는 내 뼈 속에 "
"그것을 느낍니다. 내 탐구에 찬성하여 별을 맞추는 것을 느낍니다. 내 이름은 역사의 두루마리에 기록 될 것입니다!-G-"

#: 51188213-0-2210
msgctxt "51188213-0-2210"
msgid "From Nirn to the Aether"
msgstr ""

#: 21337012-0-2205
msgctxt "21337012-0-2205"
msgid ""
"At last I near the site. Seldom have I been so impatient in my long career. "
"I spent the night at Castle Alessia, mere hours north of the battleground. "
"My excitement prevented me from sleeping more than a few minutes at a time.\n"
"\n"
"I set off at daybreak and made good time until we neared the ruins of "
"Variela Tower. My horse smelled the undead that haunt that desolate place "
"and threw me from the saddle. When I regained consciousness, Lightstep was "
"nowhere in sight. I assume my supplies are with her as well, much good they "
"will do her.\n"
"\n"
"Fortunately this journal was inside my cloak. Though it caused a painful "
"bruise when I landed on it, I am still able to take notes for my paper.\n"
"\n"
"I skirted the Variela ruins, not wishing to be eviscerated by the undead "
"shambling about. The graveyard, site of the ancient battle, is just to the "
"south. So little is known about this battle that my research should be "
"eagerly awaited. I hope to answer many questions today.\n"
"\n"
"Were the Ayleids part of a strong contingent of Elves based at Variela? Or "
"were they scouts coming from afar? And what in Julianos' name were Orcs "
"doing there? Did they too have a previously unsuspected stronghold nearby, "
"or were they a band of marauders far from home? Unearthing the graves and "
"examining the artifacts they contain should tell me much.\n"
"\n"
"I have rested here long enough. The shadows lengthen already. I will make a "
"pitiful camp in the graveyard and begin my excavations in the morning. "
"Discovery awaits!"
msgstr ""

#: 51188213-0-2205
msgctxt "51188213-0-2205"
msgid "Graveyard Research Notes"
